        "Lokai"
      ],
      "text": "Grandma Lokai was an orphan caretaker who owned her own orphanage at the top of a cliff near Hiroku Canyon. She was known to treat her guests like princes and princesses, often dressing them up in crowns, tights, and other formal attire."
    },
    {
      "body": "Grandma Lokai found ${link_0}, ${link_1}, and ${link_2} upon their separation from the rest of ${link_3}. Excited at the arrival of new guests, she dressed the trio in royal clothing and treated them like young children, referring to Toph as \"granny's little princess\". ${link_4} and ${link_5} arrived soon after, having just escaped a band of ${link_6} thieves. Delighted, Grandma Lokai ordered for more tights, robes, and crowns to be fetched.",
